surface: the S. Philip of marble which is on a pilaster on the outside of the Oratory of Orsanmichele
four saints in marble, which the same Nanni was commissioned to make by the Guild of Smiths, Carpenters, and Masons
the marble shrine, in the base of which, at the foot, there is a scene wherein S. Lo, the Farrier, is shoeing a frenzied horse, so well made that Nanni deserved much praise for it
